.TH RUSTY-SWEEPER 1 "December 2024" "rusty-sweeper 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rusty-sweeper \- a fast, interactive disk usage analyzer and cleaner for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rusty-sweeper
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rusty-sweeper
is a disk usage management utility that provides:
.IP \(bu 2
Interactive TUI with ncdu-like interface
.IP \(bu 2
Project detection and build artifact cleaning from within the TUI
.SH STATUS
Current implementation status:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBrusty-sweeper\fR launches the TUI directly
.IP \(bu 2
\fBrusty-sweeper-monitor\fR is the dedicated monitor binary
.IP \(bu 2
The configuration file is loaded and validated, but most command behavior is still driven directly by CLI flags
.IP \(bu 2
Standalone scan/clean/completion subcommands are no longer exposed on the main binary
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config =\fIPATH\fR
Path to configuration file
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information
.SH USAGE
.B rusty-sweeper
.PP
Launch the TUI with default settings.
.SH TUI KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.BR j / \[da]
Move down
.TP
.BR k / \[ua]
Move up
.TP
.BR Enter / l / \[->]
Expand/enter directory
.TP
.BR h / \[<-] / Backspace
Collapse/go up
.TP
.BR d / Delete
Delete selected
.TP
.B c
Clean project
.TP
.B s
Cycle sort order
.TP
.B /
Search
.TP
.B .
Toggle hidden files
.TP
.B r
Rescan
.TP
.B ?
Help
.TP
.BR q / Esc
Quit
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration file: \fI~/.config/rusty-sweeper/config.toml\fR
.PP
This file is currently loaded and validated on startup, but most command behavior is not yet driven from config values.
.PP
Example:
.PP
.RS
.nf
[scanner]
parallel_threads = 0
cross_filesystems = false
use_cache = true
cache_ttl = 3600

[cleaner]
project_types = ["cargo", "gradle", "npm", "maven"]
exclude_patterns = ["**/.git", "**/vendor"]
min_age_days = 7
max_depth = 10
parallel_jobs = 4

[monitor]
interval = 300
warn_threshold = 80
critical_threshold = 90
mount_points = []
notification_backend = "auto"

[tui]
color_scheme = "auto"
show_hidden = false
default_sort = "size"
large_dir_threshold = 1073741824
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/rusty-sweeper/config.toml
User configuration file
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/rusty-sweeper.pid
Monitor daemon PID file
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/rusty-sweeper/monitor.log
Monitor daemon log file
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 2
Invalid cleaner type selection
.TP
.B 5
Partial cleanup failure
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start the TUI:
.B rusty-sweeper
.TP
Start monitor daemon with custom thresholds:
.B rusty-sweeper-monitor -d -w 70 -C 85
